	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, a couple of things here...<br><br>First a foremost, just because you died three times trying to get a corpse, you should not throw in the towel on the character.<br><br>Secondly, unless you are a seasoned player (or an Iksar), there's really no reason to be on Kunark at such a low level.  I'd recommend using EQ Atlas (<a href="http://www.eqatlas.com" target=_new>http://www.eqatlas.com</a>) to scout for hunting zones that only have mobs close to your level range.  Wandering mobs in their 30s, when you are not even in your teens, can be VERY dangerous, as I guess you've found.<br><br>I'm not sure what your money problems would be with an Iksar.  As far as I know, the only thing limiting your loot is the monster(s) you kill. Race should have little, if any, correlation with loot. Here again, I think you've thrown in the towel too quickly.<br><br>I guess the best advice I can give is to pick a class you've enjoyed thus far, and play it to 20 at least.  You'll never really know what class best suits you if you never play any of them past 10.  =)<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-Maintaining the Honor of Test</td></tr>
