<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10086057811561></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10086057811561><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=10086057811561>RE: EXP Penalty?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=10086057811561#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=126085><span id=Scholar>The Honorable MentalSword</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>25 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 17th 11:16 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.11]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The EXP Penalty primarily affected Paladins and Shadow Knights.  While the penalty was not removed, per say, it was revised.  Basically, solo, you incur only a small exp loss compared to the equivalent warrior.  But in a group, the former penalty now acts as a slight EXP bonus for your entire group, because it was in groups that the Hybrid EXP penalty was causing mischief.  Verant thoroughly explained these changes back when they made them.  You might find the exact explanation in a patch message archives, though I dont really know how far back the EQLive site keeps them, if at all.<br><br>The Paladin has been very nicely reworked over the last several years and is now an excellent choice of class for someone who wants both melee and magic.  THE choice, in my opinion.  =)<br><br>Greywen Ellsidell<br>30th Rank Paladin<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-Maintaining the Honor of Test</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
